overview: The user initiated a request to significantly improve the aesthetics
  of their sleep questionnaire application, which they felt was visually
  uninspired. The assistant began by analyzing the existing codebase,
  identifying areas for improvement such as the generic color palette, plain
  layouts, and basic form elements. A new sleep-themed color palette was
  introduced, along with custom utility classes for gradients and shadows. The
  main  layout was redesigned with decorative elements and an
  improved progress indicator. All core UI components like checkboxes, radio
  buttons, sliders, and cards were enhanced with modern styling and interactive
  states. Crucially, a systematic pass was made to ensure consistent application
  of the new theme across all 14 questionnaire sections, replacing old gray
  boxes with refined card-style groupings. During the review, a React console
  error concerning  values in input fields was identified and fixed by
  modifying the  component to safely handle such values. Finally, based
  on a detailed aesthetic review, further refinements were made to standardize
  alert colors and increase the visual definition of section borders, resulting
  in a cohesive, calming, and professional user interface.
